location.Description: The geo-location where the resource lives

systemData.Description: Metadata pertaining to creation and last modification of the resource.

provisioningState.Description: Provisioning state of the link at the time the operation was called

secrets.Description: The secret values for the given RabbitMQQueue resource

host.Description: The hostname of the RabbitMQ instance

port.Description: The port of the RabbitMQ instance. Defaults to 5672

vHost.Description: The RabbitMQ virtual host (vHost) the client will connect to. Defaults to no vHost.

username.Description: The username to use when connecting to the RabbitMQ instance

resources.Description: List of the resource IDs that support the rabbitMQ resource

resourceProvisioning.Description: Specifies how the underlying service/resource is provisioned and managed. Available values are 'recipe', where Radius manages the lifecycle of the resource through a Recipe, and 'manual', where a user manages the resource and provides the values.

recipe.Description: The recipe used to automatically deploy underlying infrastructure for a link

tls.Description: Specifies whether to use SSL when connecting to the RabbitMQ instance

environment.Description: Fully qualified resource ID for the environment that the link is linked to

application.Description: Fully qualified resource ID for the application that the link is consumed by

password.Description: The password used to connect to the RabbitMQ instance

uri.Description: The connection URI of the RabbitMQ instance. Generated automatically from host, port, SSL, username, password, and vhost. Can be overridden with a custom value

id.Description: Resource id of an existing resource

name.Description: The name of the recipe within the environment to use

createdBy.Description: The identity that created the resource.

createdByType.Description: The type of identity that created the resource.

lastModifiedBy.Description: The identity that last modified the resource.

lastModifiedByType.Description: The type of identity that created the resource.

lastModifiedAt.Description: The timestamp of resource last modification (UTC)

password.Description: The password used to connect to the RabbitMQ instance

uri.Description: The connection URI of the RabbitMQ instance. Generated automatically from host, port, SSL, username, password, and vhost. Can be overridden with a custom value
